Author: COTTLE
Vol / Page: 133
Edition:
Quote: `Let 'em rip' [i.e. let them be; continue their quarrel] - This latter sentence, more brief than polite, was his favourite solution of a difficulty which proved to be a little out of his province. The word `rip', as doubtless most of my readers are aware, is formed of the initial letters of the words' requiescat in pace - rest in peace'
